{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011YU9CG3DXYderW3hhcgken","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FRDsvFttwhst8UseoVoqo5","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# MongoDB Replica Set — Change / Migration Plan\n\n**Cluster:** `mongodb` namespace  \n**Replica set name:** `mongodb-replica`  \n**Inspection date:** 2026-06-25  \n**Plan status:** REVIEW ONLY — no changes applied\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current-State Snapshot\n\n### 1.1 Replica set membership\n\n| Member | Host | Priority | Votes | Arbiter | Hidden | Delay |\n|--------|------|----------|-------|---------|--------|-------|\n| 0 | `mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | No | No | 0 s |\n| 1 | `mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | No | No | 0 s |\n| 2 | `mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | No | No | 0 s |\n\n- Protocol version: 1 (`pv1`)  \n- `writeConcernMajorityJournalDefault`: true  \n- All members are equal-weight data-bearing nodes; election is non-deterministic.  \n- Default write concern: `{ w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }` (acknowledged by primary only).\n\n### 1.2 Users and roles\n\n| User | Database | Roles |\n|------|----------|-------|\n| `admin-user` | `admin` | `clusterAdmin`, `userAdminAnyDatabase`, `readWriteAnyDatabase` |\n\n- Auth mechanisms present: SCRAM-SHA-1 **and** SCRAM-SHA-256 (both active).  \n- Only one account exists; it combines cluster-management, user-management, and unrestricted data-access in a single principal — a super-admin anti-pattern.\n\n### 1.3 Journal compressor (WiredTiger)\n\n- Configured value: **`zlib`**  \n- MongoDB 6 default: `snappy`\n\n### 1.4 Log verbosity\n\n- Configured value: **`1`** (global, all components)  \n- MongoDB default: `0`\n\n### 1.5 Slow-operation (profiler) threshold\n\n- `operationProfiling.mode`: `slowOp`  \n- `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs`: **`200`**  \n- MongoDB default: `100 ms`  \n- Current setting logs only operations slower than 200 ms; operations in the 100–199 ms band are silently dropped.\n\n### 1.6 Network binding\n\n- `net.bindIpAll: true` — mongod listens on **all interfaces**, including any externally reachable NIC.\n\n### 1.7 TLS / in-transit encryption\n\n- No TLS configuration present in `mongod.conf`; intra-cluster traffic is protected only by the keyfile (HMAC, not encryption).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Target Hardened Baseline\n\nThe following baseline is the intended post-change state. Each item below maps\nto one or more concrete actions in §3.\n\n| Control | Current value | Target value | Rationale |\n|---------|--------------|--------------|-----------|\n| Auth mechanisms | SCRAM-SHA-1 + SCRAM-SHA-256 | SCRAM-SHA-256 only | SHA-1 is deprecated; disabling it eliminates credential downgrade attacks |\n| Network binding | `bindIpAll: true` | Explicit `bindIp: localhost,<pod-IP>` | Limits the attack surface to the pod's own loopback and cluster-internal IP |\n| Super-admin account | Single account with clusterAdmin + userAdminAnyDatabase + readWriteAnyDatabase | Separate dedicated accounts with least-privilege roles | Prevents a single compromised credential from granting full data and cluster control |\n| Dedicated service accounts | None | Separate backup, monitoring, and per-application users | Follows principle of least privilege; limits blast radius of any one account compromise |\n| slowOpThresholdMs | 200 ms | 50 ms | Catches a broader range of slow queries for SLO enforcement and index-gap discovery |\n| Log verbosity | 1 (global) | 0 global, component-targeted verbosity for ACCESS and COMMAND | Reduces noise; preserves security-relevant auth/command tracing |\n| Journal compressor | zlib | snappy | Reduces write latency and CPU overhead on journal writes; zlib's extra compression ratio is rarely worth the cost for journal data |\n| Write concern default | `{ w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }` | `{ w: \"majority\", wtimeout: 5000 }` | Prevents silent data loss on primary failover |\n| Primary election control | All members priority=1 | Primary: priority=10; secondaries: priority=5 | Makes primary election deterministic; simplifies planned maintenance |\n| TLS (in-transit) | Not configured | `net.tls.mode: requireTLS` with cluster CA cert | Encrypts replication traffic and client connections; complements keyfile auth |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Required Changes\n\nChanges are ordered from lowest to highest risk. Each group can be rolled out in\na separate maintenance window.\n\n### 3.1 mongod.conf changes (requires rolling restart)\n\nA rolling restart (secondary → secondary → primary stepdown → old-primary) is\nrequired for every `mongod.conf` change. Restart each member, verify it rejoins\nas SECONDARY and catches up, then proceed to the next.\n\n#### 3.1.1 Replace zlib with snappy (journal compressor)\n\n```yaml\n# in mongod.conf — storage.wiredTiger.engineConfig\njournalCompressor: snappy     # was: zlib\n```\n\n**Risk:** Low. WiredTiger switches the compressor transparently on next\ncheckpoint write; existing data files are not rewritten. No data loss path.\n\n#### 3.1.2 Tighten network binding\n\n```yaml\n# in mongod.conf — net\nbindIp: 127.0.0.1,$(POD_IP)   # was: bindIpAll: true\n```\n\n`POD_IP` must be injected via the `status.podIP` downward-API env var in the\nStatefulSet pod spec. Alternatively, use the pod's DNS name if all callers\nresolve it.\n\n**Risk:** Medium. Any client connecting via the node's host IP or a non-pod\ninterface will lose connectivity. Audit all connection strings before applying.\n\n#### 3.1.3 Reduce global log verbosity; enable targeted component logging\n\n```yaml\n# in mongod.conf — systemLog\nverbosity: 0\ncomponent:\n  accessControl:\n    verbosity: 1    # log auth successes and failures\n  command:\n    verbosity: 1    # log slow-command details\n```\n\n**Risk:** Low. Reduces log volume; does not affect behaviour.\n\n#### 3.1.4 Lower slowOpThresholdMs\n\n```yaml\n# in mongod.conf — operationProfiling\nslowOpThresholdMs: 50    # was: 200\n```\n\n**Risk:** Low. Increases the volume of slow-op log entries; no behavioural\nchange. Monitor log storage and alerting pipelines for volume increase.\n\n#### 3.1.5 Add TLS configuration\n\n```yaml\n# in mongod.conf — net.tls\nnet:\n  tls:\n    mode: requireTLS\n    certificateKeyFile: /etc/mongo-tls/tls.pem      # combined cert+key PEM\n    CAFile: /etc/mongo-tls/ca.crt\n    clusterAuthMode: x509                             # optional: mutual TLS for replication\n```\n\nPrerequisites:\n- Generate a cluster CA and per-member certificates (subject CN = member FQDN).\n- Store them in a Kubernetes Secret and mount at `/etc/mongo-tls/`.\n- Update the StatefulSet volumeMounts accordingly.\n\n**Risk:** High. All clients (application pods, monitoring agents, ops scripts)\nmust switch to TLS connections simultaneously with the last member restart, or\nuse `allowTLS` as a transition mode first.\n\n### 3.2 Replica set reconfiguration (online, no restart required)\n\nRun `rs.reconfig()` on the primary after the rolling restart above.\n\n#### 3.2.1 Set deterministic primary priority\n\n```js\ncfg = rs.conf();\ncfg.members[0].priority = 10;   // intended primary (mongodb-replica-0)\ncfg.members[1].priority = 5;\ncfg.members[2].priority = 5;\nrs.reconfig(cfg);\n```\n\n**Risk:** Low. Triggers a single election; brief (<10 s) primary failover if\nmember-0 is not currently primary.\n\n#### 3.2.2 Harden cluster-wide write concern default\n\n```js\ncfg = rs.conf();\ncfg.settings.getLastErrorDefaults = { w: \"majority\", wtimeout: 5000 };\nrs.reconfig(cfg);\n```\n\n**Risk:** Low–Medium. Any application relying on `w:1` acknowledged writes\nwithout explicit write concern will now block until a majority acknowledges.\nTest application write latency and timeout budgets before applying in production.\n\n### 3.3 User and authentication changes (online, no restart required)\n\n#### 3.3.1 Disable SCRAM-SHA-1\n\n```js\n// Run on primary as admin-user\ndb.adminCommand({\n  setParameter: 1,\n  authenticationMechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"]\n});\n```\n\nThis is a live setParameter call; it takes effect immediately without restart.\nHowever, the setting is not persisted to `mongod.conf`; add it to ensure it\nsurvives a restart:\n\n```yaml\n# in mongod.conf — security\nsecurity:\n  authorization: enabled\n  keyFile: /etc/mongo-keyfile/keyfile\n  mechanismCache:\n    authenticationMechanisms: [SCRAM-SHA-256]\n```\n\n**Risk:** Any client or driver using SCRAM-SHA-1 explicitly will fail to\nauthenticate. Audit driver configurations before applying.\n\n#### 3.3.2 Create least-privilege service accounts\n\nCreate dedicated accounts before removing permissions from `admin-user`.\n\n```js\n// Cluster/DBA admin — can manage cluster and users but NOT read application data\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n  user: \"dba-admin\",\n  pwd: \"<strong-random-password>\",\n  roles: [\"clusterAdmin\", \"userAdminAnyDatabase\"]\n});\n\n// Backup operator — can read all data for backups, cannot write\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n  user: \"backup-user\",\n  pwd: \"<strong-random-password>\",\n  roles: [\"backup\"]\n});\n\n// Monitoring agent — cluster-level read-only metrics\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n  user: \"monitoring-user\",\n  pwd: \"<strong-random-password>\",\n  roles: [\"clusterMonitor\", { role: \"read\", db: \"local\" }]\n});\n\n// Per-application user — scoped to the application's own database only\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"<app-database>\").createUser({\n  user: \"app-user\",\n  pwd: \"<strong-random-password>\",\n  roles: [{ role: \"readWrite\", db: \"<app-database>\" }]\n});\n```\n\n#### 3.3.3 Strip readWriteAnyDatabase from admin-user\n\nOnce the dedicated accounts are verified, remove the overly broad data-access\nrole from the original account:\n\n```js\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").updateUser(\"admin-user\", {\n  roles: [\"clusterAdmin\", \"userAdminAnyDatabase\"]\n  // readWriteAnyDatabase removed\n});\n```\n\n**Risk:** Any application still connecting as `admin-user` will lose write\naccess to application databases. Complete the migration to `app-user` first.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Execution Sequence Summary\n\n| Step | Action | Restart required | Estimated risk |\n|------|--------|-----------------|----------------|\n| 1 | Create `dba-admin`, `backup-user`, `monitoring-user`, `app-user` accounts | No | Low |\n| 2 | Switch clients off `admin-user` to appropriate service accounts | No | Medium |\n| 3 | Strip `readWriteAnyDatabase` from `admin-user` | No | Low (after step 2) |\n| 4 | Rolling restart: switch compressor snappy, lower slowOpThresholdMs to 50, adjust log verbosity | Yes (rolling) | Low |\n| 5 | Rolling restart: tighten `bindIp` | Yes (rolling) | Medium |\n| 6 | `rs.reconfig()`: set member priorities and majority write concern default | No | Low–Medium |\n| 7 | Provision TLS certificates and secrets | No | Low (prep only) |\n| 8 | Rolling restart: enable `requireTLS` (after client migration to TLS) | Yes (rolling) | High |\n| 9 | Disable SCRAM-SHA-1 (setParameter + mongod.conf) | Rolling restart for persistence | Medium |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Pre-Change Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] All three pods are in `Running 1/1` state and replica set has a stable primary.\n- [ ] Baseline slow-op log volume documented (for post-change comparison after step 4).\n- [ ] All application connection strings identified and mapped to credentials.\n- [ ] TLS certificates generated, validated against the cluster CA, and stored in a Secret.\n- [ ] Backup taken (or `mongodump` snapshot verified) before any restart.\n- [ ] Monitoring alerts for replica set election events are active.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Rollback Notes\n\n- **mongod.conf changes:** revert the ConfigMap to the previous version and\n  perform another rolling restart.\n- **User changes:** roles and accounts can be re-applied or restored via\n  `db.updateUser` / `db.createUser` without downtime.\n- **rs.reconfig():** revert with a second `rs.reconfig()` restoring the\n  original `settings` block; keep a copy of `rs.conf()` output before any change.\n- **SCRAM-SHA-1 disablement:** re-add `SCRAM-SHA-1` to\n  `authenticationMechanisms` via `setParameter` immediately if client failures\n  are observed.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1269,"cache_read_input_tokens":32068,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1269},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1de6554f-9867-46d0-9d7a-87c134a1d72e","uuid":"27c07812-b17b-4155-99a0-42bd3e58eeca","request_id":"req_011CcQ5hBXPaPxsB6qpTiZLE"}
